RACE.RACE_TEXT: FOXFIELD RACE 1 2 1/8M Hurdle CR: N/A. Maiden Claiming Purse 20000. TO BE RUN OVER NATIONAL FENCES FOR MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 142 lbs.; Four Year Olds, 150 lbs.; Older, 154 lbs. Claiming Price $15,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: EYE OF GUNFIGHTER led from the start, set the pace early, and held off challengers before the last hurdle to prevail in the stretch. ICANDOTHAT tracked the leader early, settled off the pace at one mile, bid in the stretch, and came up second best. GREYLOVER settled midpack, exchanging positions with close competitors, made a bid before the last hurdle but couldn't maintain the pace. SECRET SOULMATE stalked the leader after one mile, gave chase before the last hurdle and faded before the stretch. CODIGO ran just behind the leaders early, gained ground 5/8 from home, moved into the 4-path to bid before the last hurdle, then faded. MCSTEAMY settled 4th to 5th behind the leader in early going, maintained position until fading back before the last hurdle. ICE BAR ran off the pace, remaining well behind the lead, and was never a factor. BELLARMINE HALL ran at the back of the field and was never a factor. ROYAL REGATTA was anxious at the start, ran at the back of the field, pulled up before the last hurdle and walked off.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: FOXFIELD RACE 3 2 1/8M Hurdle CR: N/A. Maiden Special Weight Purse 30000. TO BE RUN OVER NATIONAL FENCES FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 141 lbs.; Four Year Olds, 149 lbs.; Older, 153 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: AFRAID NOT set the pace at the start, led throughout the race by one to two lengths, held off challengers before the last hurdle, and pulled away in the stretch. LACEY UNDERALL tracked the leader throughout the race within one to two lengths, made a bid at the top of the stretch, but finished second best. LADY'S GAME (GB) raced mid pack early, exchanging positions with close competitors mid race, moved into contention before the last hurdle, but was outpaced in the stretch. TANKA TOUGH was just off the pace early, maintained position until just before the last hurdle, bid at the top of the stretch, but faded in the stretch drive. FOX IN THE PARK (IRE) settled behind early, moved up in a bid before the last hurdle, then fell behind in the stretch. FRACING HOT raced toward the back in early going, gained ground after the 6th hurdle, then faded after the 8th to finish well behind the leader. LOVE SAGA ran with multiple competitors just behind the pace during the first mile-and-a-half, gained some ground before the last hurdle, entered the stretch in the back, and eased to the finish. NOWYOUSCAN'TLEAVE ran in the back of the field from the start, never gained ground, pulled up before the last hurdle and walked off. FUSEE DE POCHE (IRE) started well just off the pace, maintained for the first mile, then faded back, pulled up before the last hurdle, and walked off. READY SET SHOP ran at the back from the start, never gained ground, and pulled up after 6th hurdle and walked off.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: FOXFIELD RACE 4 2 1/8M Hurdle CR: N/A. Maiden Special Weight Purse 30000. TO BE RUN OVER NATIONAL FENCES FOR MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 142 lbs.; Four Year Olds, 150 lbs.; Older, 154 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: GARRISON FOREST (IRE) broke mid pack, ran evenly throughout the race, rallied after the 9th hurdle to pass front runners and overcame the leader in the stretch for the win. ACTIVE DUTY (FR) started mid pack, gained ground at the one mile, led before the final hurdle and at the top of the stretch, but was outpaced in the stretch by the winner. LOOK NORTH stalked the leader through the first mile, gained the lead after 6 hurdles, and lost ground before the last hurdle to finish third best. KARL CARES started toward the back, gained ground 5/8 from home, remained middle of the field, and surpassed his nearest competitor in the stretch. HIGH DEFF (FR) started mid field, made a small gain to third place before the last hurdle, entered the stretch in fourth place but was outrun by KARL CARES. VINTAGE YEAR ran out the back, made no significant gains, and was never a factor. PARQUETRY was consistently off the pace, running middle of the field through the first mile-and-a-half then lost significant ground after the 8th hurdle. RACAVAN (IRE) started well just behind the leaders, held ground through a mile-and-a-half, then lost ground after the 8th hurdle to ultimately finish last. I AM FORTUNATA (IRE) started well and went out to an early lead, tracking wide around the course through the first mile, began tiring 5/8 from home, pulled up before the last hurdle and walked off. GOSPEL WAY ran in the back of the field from the start, made a small gain after a mile-and-a-quarter, fell behind again and pulled up before last hurdle and walked off.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: FOXFIELD RACE 5 2 1/4M Hurdle CR: N/A. Handicap Purse 25000. TO BE RUN OVER NATIONAL FENCES FOR FOUR YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH ARE RATED 110 OR LOWER. The highest rated horse will be assigned 158 lbs. with all other races adjusted accordingly based on the current ratings. Minimum weight 140 lbs., not including app rentice allowances.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: ARROWHEART broke mid pack, kept pace with the lead early, assumed the lead at one mile, and never relinquished to win handily. BALTIMORE KID (IRE) started midfield, gained ground after one mile, held to the pace, came within striking distance 1/4 from home but faded in the stretch. NEW APPOINTMENT (IRE) was unruly before the start and broke late, gained ground early to approach the field, ran even after one mile, and gained ground before the last hurdle to achieve better placement. OSCAR WINNER broke midfield, ran even through most of the race, gained ground before the last hurdle but faded in the stretch. DURRAGH (IRE) ran out the back at the start, gained ground after one mile, held position through the 9th hurdle then lost ground and faded. MR. CONNECTICUT started midfield, faded to the back early, pulled up after the 7th hurdle and walked off. SEISMIC WAVE kept the pace early, stumbled and lost rider upon landing at the 6th hurdle, pushing LEFT BANK to the inside, resulting in LEFT BANK going off course. LEFT BANK held an early lead, relinquished at the one mile to ARROWHEART, and went off course at the 6th hurdle after SEISMIC WAVE stumbled. MARSHELLA (IRE) ran just off the pace early, was running to the inside of LEFT BANK at the 6th hurdle and was pushed off course on the landing side of the 6th hurdle by LEFT BANK after SEISMIC WAVE stumbled. SEIZING THE DREAM ran off the pace, fell at the third hurdle, and walked off.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: FOXFIELD RACE 6 2 1/4M Hurdle CR: N/A. Handicap Purse 35000. TO BE RUN OVER NATIONAL FENCES FOR FOUR YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH ARE RATED 120 OR LOWER. The highest rated horse will be assigned 158 lbs. with all other races adjusted accordingly based on the current ratings. Minimum weight 140 lbs., not including app rentice allowances.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: WHO'S COUNTING kept pace and the stalked leader, made a bid before the last hurdle, overtaking WICKED WEST to enter the stretch in front and outdistanced all other competitors. PRESENCE OF MIND (IRE) ran in the middle of the field from the start, gained ground at the 10th hurdle, made a bid before the final hurdle but was unable to gain ground to win. ANIMAL KINGSTON held steady in the middle of the field from the start, rallied approaching the last hurdle, overtaking WICKED WEST (IRE) but unable to outdistance WHO'S COUNTING and PRESENCE OF MIND (IRE). WICKED WEST (IRE) set the pace from the start, maintaining the lead until approaching the last hurdle when he was overtaken by the top three contenders and faded in the stretch. GO POKE THE BEAR started in back, gained to midfield by one mile, maintained position but had no late rally. ZABEEL CHAMPION (GB) held pace with the leader until 3/4 from home, then faded after the 10th hurdle. HE'LL DO ran behind from the start, never gained ground, and had no late rally. L'OR DES ROSES (FR) ran out the back of the field from the start, tired before the 10th hurdle, and was eased to the finish.
